alert.note: Alert for Northern Ventura County Mountains (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 19 at 11:58AM PST until November 19 at 11:00PM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM PST THIS EVENING... * WHAT...North winds 25 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph expected. Isolated gusts to 70 mph possible for Interstate 5 Corridor. * WHERE...Northern Ventura County Mountains. * WHEN...Until 11 PM PST this evening. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as trees and power lines. Power outages are likely. Travel will be difficult, especially for drivers of high profile vehicles. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Advisory level northeast winds may continue at times Monday or Tuesday.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around large trees. If possible, remain in your home and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
